---- MODULE MCDieHarder ----
EXTENDS ModuleNameForPreviousModelDieHarder  -- Replace with the name/path where module DieHarder is defined.

(******************************************************************************)
(* The following definitions duplicate the original 'Die Hard' problem,          *)
(* extending it to handle multiple jugs and capacities instead of just one    .*)
(* To have TLC find a solution, we must tell it what values to use for           *) 
(* constant parameters Jug (which is function-valued), Capacity                  *)  
(******************************************************************************)
CONSTANTS Goal     == <value> -- Specify the value in your configuration file.   
                          (* The goal amount of liquid we want from jugs*)       . 
Jug         == UNCHANGED <<ModuleNameForPreviousModelDieHarder>>              ,  
                           (** Extract Jug set as is, assuming it's defined there.*).     
Capacity    == MCCapacity                                                      ,   
                          (* The capacities of the jugs.*)                         . 
SPECIFICATION Spec                                                                       -- Main specification to prove correctness/liveness etc..  
INVARIANTS TypeOK NotSolved                                                             -- Invariants for proving properties, e.g., no deadlocks or livelocks     )    ,      (** This line is just a placeholder and needs actual invariants defined.*).  .       == <value>-- Specify the value in your configuration file
